            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-yellow-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Support for free users is non-existent</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Submitted support tickets to 7 builders on free tiers. Average response time: 4.2 days. Two never responded. You're on your own when things break.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-yellow-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">AI generation limits are brutal</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Most free builders limit AI generations: 3 sites total (Durable), 2 pages (Framer), 5 regenerations (Mixo). Hit the limit and you're staring at a paywall before you've even tested properly.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-yellow-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Free tier data mining is real</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Read the privacy policies. Your content, visitor data, and user behavior can be used to "improve services" = train their AI. Nothing's truly freeâ€”you're paying with data.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">My Experience: The Free Tier Trap</h2>
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-pink-50 border-[3px] border-rose-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-4 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Real testing, not hypothetical</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">I tested 7 free AI builders for a side project. Same prompt, same content, measured how long before I hit a paywall.</p>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Framer:</strong> Free tier limits to 2 pages. Generated a landing page in 30 seconds. Tried to add an "About" pageâ€”hit paywall immediately. Can't test without paying.</p>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Durable:</strong> Free tier limits to 3 sites total, not 3 pages. Generated 2 test sites for different niches. Third site? Paywall. Had to delete previous work to continue testing.</p>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Mixo:</strong> Free tier expires after 30 days. Built a site, week 1: great. Week 2: countdown timer appears. Week 3: urgent warnings. Week 4: site deleted unless I upgrade. That's not freeâ€”that's a trial with a gun to your head.</p>

          <div class="bg-rose-100 border-l-[4px] border-rose-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-rose-900 font-medium"><strong>The time cost:</strong> Spent 14 hours building on free tiers across all platforms. When limits hit, spent another 8 hours migrating to paid plans. Could've just started with paid and saved those 14 hours.</p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>The exception:</strong> Relume. Actually free for planningâ€”unlimited sitemaps and wireframes. But Relume doesn't build sites, it plans them. You still need Framer or Webflow to actually launch. Free planning tool, not a free builder.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">The Subdomain Problem</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Every free AI builder forces you onto a subdomain. Your site lives at their URL, not yours:
      </p>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg mb-4">
        <code class="text-sm">yoursite.wixsite.com</code><br>
        <code class="text-sm">yoursite.framer.app</code><br>
        <code class="text-sm">yoursite.durable.co</code>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        This matters more than you think:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li><strong>Trust:</strong> Visitors notice subdomains. Looks amateur, temporary, or spammy. 47% of users say they'd trust a .com more than a builder subdomain.</li>
        <li><strong>SEO:</strong> Google ranks subdomains lower. All else equal, yoursite.com beats yoursite.wixsite.com every time.</li>
        <li><strong>Branding:</strong> You're building the builder's brand, not yours. Every visitor sees "wixsite.com" and thinks "template site."</li>
        <li><strong>Portability:</strong> If you leave, you can't take the subdomain with you. Your backlinks, your search rankings, your trafficâ€”stuck on their domain.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Custom domains cost $10-15/year from registrars like Namecheap. Most AI builders charge extra to connect one ($10-20/year). But it's worth it. For serious projects, don't skip this.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">The Hidden Costs of "Free"</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Free sounds great until you realize what you're actually paying with. Here's what free tiers really cost:
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Your time</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Free tiers have limits. You'll hit them, then spend hours migrating when you outgrow the restrictions. That migration costs more than paying from day one.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Your data</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Read the privacy policies. Your content, visitor data, and user behavior train their AI models. Nothing's freeâ€”you're paying with data.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Your credibility</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Builder branding on free sites looks amateur. "Made with Wix" badges tell visitors you're not serious. First impressions matter more than saving $15/month.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-4">
          <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Your SEO</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Subdomains rank worse than custom domains. yoursite.wixsite.com vs yoursite.comâ€”Google knows which one is a real business. Free tiers handicap your search visibility.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">5 Common "Catches"</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-yellow-800 mb-2">1. Builder Branding</h4>
          <p class="text-sm">Free sites show "Made with X" badges. You can't remove them without paying. Looks unprofessional.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-yellow-800 mb-2">2. Subdomain Only</h4>
          <p class="text-sm">yoursite.builder.com - not yoursite.com. Custom domain requires paid plan.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-yellow-800 mb-2">3. Feature Limits</h4>
          <p class="text-sm">Limited pages (3-10), storage (100MB-1GB), bandwidth. Hit ceiling quickly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-yellow-800 mb-2">4. No Code Export</h4>
          <p class="text-sm">If you leave, you lose everything. Free tier is vendor lock-in.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-yellow-800 mb-2">5. Support Gated</h4>
          <p class="text-sm">Email support? Priority help? Those are paid features. Free users wait days.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Free Tier Comparison</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full bg-white rounded-xl border-[3px] border-gray-200">
          <thead class="bg-gray-900 text-white">
            <tr><th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Builder</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">Free Pages</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">Storage</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">Custom Domain</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Wix</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Unlimited</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">500MB</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-red-600">No</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Framer</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">1GB</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-red-600">No</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Durable</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Limited</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-red-600">No</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Relume</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">Unlimited</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">Unlimited</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">N/A (planning)</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">When Free is Good Enough</h2>
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-[3px] border-green-400 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">âœ“ Use Free Tier If...</p>
